\subsection{Main Results}
\label{sec:mainresults}

Table~\ref{tab:main_results} presents performance on the Ch\'{a}k\c{s}u
test set ($n{=}336$; 51 Glaucoma / 285 Normal).  The most striking
result is that the DINOv3 source model, trained solely on Western AIROGS
data, achieves an AUROC of \textbf{0.846} on Indian retinal images---only
5.4 points below the in-domain supervised oracle (0.900).  This
represents an 85\% gap closure relative to the untuned pretrained
backbone with a random task head (AUROC 0.414).  A sanity check on the
