\subsection{IM Loss Mode Collapse Analysis}
\label{sec:imloss_collapse}

The Run-6 adaptation yielded Sensitivity 0.980 / Specificity 0.042,
the signature of full minority-class collapse.  We identify two
interacting causes.

\textbf{Cause 1: Mismatched loss scopes.}
$\mathcal{L}_{\mathrm{ent}}$ was applied over the \emph{uncertain} half
of each batch, while $\mathcal{L}_{\mathrm{div}} = -\mathcal{H}(\mathbb{E}[p])$
was applied over the \emph{full} batch.  With Ch\'{a}k\c{s}u's 86\%
Normal prevalence, the confident half anchors the batch marginal at
$\bar{p} \approx [0.86,\,0.14]$.  Maximising $-\mathcal{H}(\bar{p})$
towards $[0.5,\,0.5]$ therefore requires the uncertain half to shift
towards Glaucoma.  Entropy minimisation then locks in those predictions
with high confidence.

\textbf{Cause 2: Biased pseudo-labels under domain shift.}
From epoch 10, a progressive self-training loss used source-model
confidence to gate pseudo-labels.  Under domain shift the source head
is miscalibrated, generating biased pseudo-labels that reinforce the
already-collapsing predictions.

\textbf{Proposed corrections (Run-7, in progress):}
(i)~Apply both $\mathcal{L}_{\mathrm{ent}}$ and
$\mathcal{L}_{\mathrm{div}}$ to the same uncertain sample pool;
(ii)~Add class-prior regulariser
$\mathcal{L}_{\mathrm{bal}} = \mathrm{KL}(\bar{p}_{\mathrm{full}}
\,\|\,[0.85,\,0.15])$, $\lambda{=}1.0$;
(iii)~Disable pseudo-label loss entirely ($\lambda_{\mathrm{psl}}{=}0$).
These corrections are mathematically guaranteed to raise the energy cost
of any full-class-collapse solution.

